				<td colspan="2"><span>I actually like the combat system of Horizons.  As well as the build in macro system.
<br />

<br />
When in combat, your character always stays within mele range (if you are using mele attacks).  That means you can hit left or right arrow to move around the mob easily.  One thing I hate about EQ mele is having to worry about distance from mob, none in Horizons.
<br />

<br />
Built in macro system is sweet, a little too much as it can be used to create AFK macros, but nice none the less.  It can target nearest mob, equip bow/crossbow, fire it, equip sword &amp; shield or 2hand sword (you get the idea) and attack the mob.
<br />

<br />
Special attacks start at the low end.  Mele stuns, power swings, and more, all at the click of a button simular to EQ /disc abilities; they're even on timers.
<br />

<br />
Ultimately the reason I left the game is financial.</span></td>
