				<td colspan="2"><span>I have been having fun puttering around Horizons for the last month or so.  It's a low key sort of game that doesn't require you to spend hours at a stretch in front of the keyboard in order to accomplish anything.  It's a nice break from raiding, which is mostly all I do in EQ now.
<br />

<br />
It is definetly not nearly as much of a grouping game as EQ.  You can accomplish almost everything on your own if you want, though I have lately been duoing with other people to be a little more productive and see a different side of the game.  You can interact with other people as much or as little as you want - there is no /ooc so unless you join one of the public channels you don't get the mindless blather of zones like PoK unless you want it.  
<br />

<br />
One of the attractions for me, given I despise EQ's absurd corpse retrieval system, is the Death Points approach in Horizons.  When you die you can either get rezzed on the spot if a rezzer is nearby or you can recall to you bind point and accumulate a Death Point, which affects your abilities negatively until it wears off.  I can never understand why people in EQ think wasting hours and hours of your gaming time on CRs is any way fun... but that's just me.
<br />

<br />
It strikes me that it was released about six months before it should have been but with EQ2 and WoW coming out I doubt they had a choice about getting it on the market.  
<br />
</span></td>
